duce the correct sequence of the amino acids that make up a protein. Therefore, to perform all these tasks they use ready-made natural enzymes which have been placed at mankind's disposal. The more research is performed, the more enzymes are discovered, l
iterally gift-wrapped inside micro-organisms as major labor-saving devices, easily located where any scientist can obtain them.
